109 L’un l’altro ha spento; ed è giunta la spada 110 col pasturale, e l’un con l’altro insieme 111 per viva forza mal convien che vada;
112 però che, giunti, l’un l’altro non teme: 113 se non mi credi, pon mente a la spiga, 114 ch’ogn’ erba si conosce per lo seme.

query.result:
**English:**
109 One has extinguished the other; and now the sword 110 is joined with the shepherd's staff, and one with the other 111 by main force must ill agree;
112 because, once joined, one does not fear the other: 113 if you do not believe me, look at the ear of corn, 114 for every plant is known by its seed.
**Sanskrit:**
